The paper deals with a compressed sensing framework and focuses on the design of a sensing matrix for sparse source reconstruction in a system where the source-to-sensor channel and the sensor-to-decoder communication channel are noisy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of practical sparse reconstruction algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the design method and proposes a stochastic optimization method, which suggests that it may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
